The number of AIDS patients and HIV carriers in  Japan has risen to 1,546, with 70 more reported in the March-April period,  officials said Tuesday.
The health and welfare ministry said that 44 of the 70 in a quarterly  survey were men and 26 were women.
It did not specify the total numbers of patients with Acquired Immune  Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS) or those carrying the Human Immune-deficiency Virus  which breaks down the body's immune system.
